  "body": "Start a container:\r\n```\r\nsudo ./bin/ctr pull docker.io/library/alpine:latest \r\nsudo ./bin/ctr run -t docker.io/library/alpine:latest test ash -l\r\n```\r\nand then in another window:\r\n```\r\nsudo ./bin/ctr t exec --exec-id foo -t test echo foop\r\nfoop\r\nERRO[0000] resize pty                                    error=\"cannot resize a stopped container: unknown\"\r\n\r\n```\r\nThis will work and then hang/block. You can also use `ash -l` and then `Ctrl-C`, in that case I do not get the `resize pty` error, it just stops after the `Ctrl-C`.\r\n\r\nExiting the original shell (from `ctr run`) causes the exec to then exit correctly. ",
